# [TEAS](../wg/teas.html)

## Summary
The TEAS Working Group met to discuss several key traffic engineering initiatives, including power-aware traffic engineering, RSVP-TE extensions for native IP and SRv6 networks, Multipath Traffic Engineering (MP-TE) architecture and its corresponding signaling and data models, Multicast Traffic Engineering (MC-TE), carrying 5G network slice identifiers in IP headers, and high-performance computing/AI (HPC/AI) data models. 

Polls were conducted to gauge working group interest in power-aware traffic engineering and MP-TE, showing solid support for further exploration of both topics.

