## Decisions and Action Items
* **Power-Aware Traffic Engineering**: The chairs will initiate a formal call for adoption on the mailing list. Authors need to maintain coordination with the GREEN WG and address simplification comments raised during the session.
* **IP-TE and SRv6-TE Tunnels**: Discussion on the implications of introducing RSVP-TE state into segment routing networks will be brought to the SPRING WG.
* **Multipath Traffic Engineering (MP-TE)**: Based on strong poll results, the chairs will initiate adoption calls for the MP-TE architecture, RSVP-TE signaling, and YANG model drafts.
* **5G Network Slice Identifiers**: The presenter will follow up on the mailing list regarding header overhead concerns and alternative QoS mapping designs.

